The paper discusses the learning process of feed-forward neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the emergence of local codes in neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper uses generated input and output data, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the resilience of localist encoding to noisy networks, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
